@@yThe Sandwright Causeway@@N~
@@yThis leg of the eastern road is scored with old wheel tracks, deep enough to show how heavily it has been trusted over the years.

@@bA sharp desert breeze sweeps along the straightaway and whistles through broken trade-post timbers half-buried beside the route.

@@yThe horizon shimmers in bands of @@bblue@@y and @@ygold@@y, making distance uncertain and the next rise feel farther than it should.@@N

@@yTo the sides, untouched dunes promise danger and opportunity, but the main road remains an intentional, unbroken guide toward the far east.@@N

